[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hello,<br>\nI have a question about r4l convention:<br>\nif we are guaranteed that an Option is a Some() and not None, can we use unwrap() for readability?<br>\nexample:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo_opt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">opt</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo_opt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo_opt</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">take</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Otherwise the code becomes ugly with pointless error returning:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo_opt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">opt</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo_opt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo_opt</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">take</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">ok_or</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">EINVAL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 519393311,
        "sender_full_name": "Joel Fernandes",
        "timestamp": 1747749619
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In your first code snippet you can write <code>bar = foo;</code> inside the if, right?</p>",
        "id": 519402881,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1747751843
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>actually let me show the full code, it is some code I was discussing with Danilo on the list:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">second</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">second_fwsec_image</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">// Take ownership of the option</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">second_ref</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">first</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">pci_at</span><span class=\"p\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">second</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_mut</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">first_fwsec_image</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pci_at_image</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">second_ref</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">setup_falcon_data</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">pdev</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">pci_at</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">first</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inspect_err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dev_err</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">pdev</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ref</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"Falcon data setup failed: {:?}</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">))</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Vbios</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">fwsec_image</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">second</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">take</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">else</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">dev_err</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">pdev</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ref</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"s\">\"Missing required images for falcon data setup, skipping</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">EINVAL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Here, I cannot do <code>Ok(Vbios { fwsec_image: *second_ref; })</code> because the Image type does not have the Copy trait.  I believe I will run into the same problem with your suggestion as well. I cannot just do <code>= foo</code> because it will require implementing the Copy trait, which is expensive for this object since it is a large struct. Instead I'd like to do:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Vbios</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">fwsec_image</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">second</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">take</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"p\">})</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which is safe because the <code>Option</code> is guaranteed to be a <code>Some()</code>. Hope that is Ok?</p>",
        "id": 519403739,
        "sender_full_name": "Joel Fernandes",
        "timestamp": 1747752063
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Actually, I don't need the <code>take()</code> even, this also works:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Vbios</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">fwsec_image</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">second</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">})</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 519408175,
        "sender_full_name": "Joel Fernandes",
        "timestamp": 1747753132
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah Danilo made a nice suggestion which now does not even need the unwrap, since unwrapping is implicit in the Some() expression:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">second</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">first</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">pci_at</span><span class=\"p\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">second_fwsec_image</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">first_fwsec_image</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pci_at_image</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">second</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">setup_falcon_data</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">pdev</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">pci_at</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">first</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inspect_err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dev_err</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">pdev</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ref</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"Falcon data setup failed: {:?}</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">))</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Vbios</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">fwsec_image</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">second</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>So that solves it nicely :)</p>",
        "id": 519410653,
        "sender_full_name": "Joel Fernandes",
        "timestamp": 1747753728
    },
